```solidity
function withdrawBalance() public {
    uint amountToWithdraw = userBalances[msg.sender];
    userBalances[msg.sender] = 0;
    (bool success, ) = msg.sender.call.value(amountToWithdraw)("");
    require(success);
}
```

This way, even if the external contract calls back into the `withdrawBalance` function, the contract state has already been updated, and the attacker cannot drain the contract of more funds than they are entitled to.

